reviews.review_text: One of the best shows ever The Dead opened in the afternoon with an absolute killer Morning Dew a rare opener. It was hot an sunny and they played on and on, hour after hour, three sets of bliss. Mr. Natural purple blotter was everywhere. The Allman Brothers played in the evening and then Jerry came out and jammed on the encore. The next day they reversed places.

sweet memories This was my third show, (yes, I'm getting old) -I'd already been enveloped in the joy of the day before. Got some good photos on the ninth. This is an AUD recording, not a board, but it's worth hearing. Phil's bass comes through really strongly for some reason...maybe the taper was close to his monitor. It was a very special, magical afternoon and night- I'll never forget it. The performance live was better than what you get from the SNBDs loaded here, they were so ON I was in heaven. Listening to the first few bars of Morning Dew again literally gives me goosebumps. Even though some of the magic from how extremely tight they were is lost in these recordings, it's still a great stream!
